#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn10.2"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn10.2:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 10 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 10 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn10.2:0.2"
msgid "1. Indakavagga "
msgstr "1. With Indaka "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 2. Sakkanāmasutta → sakkasuttaṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "sn10.2:0.3"
msgid "2. Sakkanāmasutta "
msgstr "2. With a Spirit Named Sakka "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn10.2:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati gijjhakūṭe pabbate. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, on the Vulture’s Peak Mountain. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
# NOTE: BB doesn’t comment on the name. A variant in the title says just Sakka, and he is addressed as Sakka by the Buddha. Perhaps he is called “named sakka” to differentiate him from THE Sakka.
msgctxt "sn10.2:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho sakkanāmako yakkho yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi: "
msgstr "Then a spirit named Sakka went up to the Buddha, and addressed him in verse: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc2, verse-num-sc805
msgctxt "sn10.2:2.1"
msgid "“Sabbaganthappahīnassa, "
msgstr "“You’ve given up all ties, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.2:2.2"
msgid "vippamuttassa te sato; "
msgstr "and are fully freed. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.2:2.3"
msgid "Samaṇassa na taṃ sādhu, "
msgstr "It’s not a good idea for you, ascetic, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: yadaññamanusāsasī”ti → yadaññamanusāsatīti (bj, s1-3, km, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn10.2:2.4"
msgid "yadaññamanusāsasī”ti. "
msgstr "to be instructing others.” "

# NOTE: https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/teaching-from-compassion-and-attachment/3619
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3, verse-num-sc806
msgctxt "sn10.2:3.1"
msgid "“Yena kenaci vaṇṇena, "
msgstr "“No matter what the apparent reason "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.2:3.2"
msgid "saṃvāso sakka jāyati; "
msgstr "why people are together, Sakka, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.2:3.3"
msgid "Na taṃ arahati sappañño, "
msgstr "it’s unworthy for a wise person "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.2:3.4"
msgid "manasā anukampituṃ. "
msgstr "to not think of the other with compassion. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.445, sc4, verse-num-sc807
msgctxt "sn10.2:4.1"
msgid "Manasā ce pasannena, "
msgstr "If you instruct others "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.2:4.2"
msgid "yadaññamanusāsati; "
msgstr "with a mind clear and confident, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.2:4.3"
msgid "Na tena hoti saṃyutto, "
msgstr "your compassion and empathy "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: yānukampā → sānukampā (bj, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn10.2:4.4"
msgid "yānukampā anuddayā”ti. "
msgstr "don’t create attachments.”"

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
